ts\nscatter become smaller by 80% per a mass doubling scale if EGs evolve only\nthrough major dry merger. Our result, although limited by a number statistics\nat the massive end, is consistent with the picture that major dry merging is an\nimportant mechanism for the evolution for EGs at M > 10^{11.4} M_{\\odot}, but\nless important at the lower mass range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Feb 2013 07:42:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Mar 2013 20:02:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
